CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 7, 1961, pg. A32 reads: "1961's national League Champs - ...The right photo shows the 1960 World Champions, the Pittsburgh Pirates, congratulating the 1961 National League Champions. Shown are, left to right: Pirate Dick Stuart, Cincinnati's Bob Purkey, Pittsburgh catcher Smokey Burgess, the Reds' Vada Pinson, Jerry Lynch and Leo Cardenes, and Pirate Joe Christopher. - "Teenie" Harris Photos"
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Pirates baseball players Dick Stuart, Smokey Burgess, and Joe Christopher, shaking hands with Cincinnati Reds players Vida Pinson and Leo Cardenas and Jerry Lynch inside Crosley Field, Cincinnati, another version
